post_text: The Peer Model Program within the Play and Learn (PAL) Preschool Center provides children with identified learning challenges and their non-disabled peers to attend the same academically and socially enriching classroom learning environment. post_text: Play and Learn (PAL) is an integrated inclusive licensed preschool program providing the highest quality education to children with identified learning challenges and their Peer Model non-disabled peers, three years of age until eligible for Kindergarten. Students enjoy a safe and nurturing environment and personalized attention from state-licensed teachers and highly trained educational assistants. Developmentally appropriate activities including art, motor skills, and language development, are provided within a structured learning environment where children have the opportunity to build self-esteem and positive social experiences. Learn more at https://www.maranausd.org/PAL #maranaschools

post_text: #MUSDcongrats to DMK-8 Music & Band Teacher Mrs. Karlena on this wonderful recognition! All #MUSDstudents can watch her lesson video https://youtu.be/N7hGoolYVno and use objects from around the house to explore melody and music composition! #MUSDstaysConnected
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
General 6-12 Lesson Plan: Visual Representation to Reinforce Music Literacy | CMA Foundation

Dove Mountain CSTEM K-8 School
September 4 at 8:16 AM ·

Congratulations to Mrs. Karlena Leal, one of Dove Mountain’s amazing K-8 General Music and Band Teachers, who had a lesson and video chosen by the CMA: Country Music Foundation-United Voices for Music Education Initiative to feature on their CMA Foundation YouTube page! As part of her creative lesson for teaching students about making music, Mrs. Leal’s video and lesson plan showcases her unique method of using common household items to teach students how to visually represent music notation, aural identification, and melodic fragments in composition. Dove Mountain CSTEM K-8 is extremely proud of Mrs. Leal and the contribution to sharing with other music colleagues and their students across the United States! #UnitedVoicesforME

post_text: Allocate Your Public School Tax Credit To Marana Unified School District. Donate in person or securely and conveniently online. As an Arizona tax payer, you can allocate your public school tax credit by making a donation of up to $200 / individual and $400 / married couple. This will result in a dollar-for-dollar tax credit when you file your state return. What better way to ensure Arizona's future than by investing in our young leaders? MUSD will use your donation to fund after-school tutoring, student athletics, field trips and other areas of greatest need. Learn more: http://www.maranausd.org/taxcredit ‪#‎maranaschools‬ ‪#‎aztaxcredit‬

post_text: Play and Learn (PAL) is an integrated inclusive licensed preschool program providing the highest quality education to children with identified learning challenges and their Peer Model non-disabled peers, three years of age until eligible for Kindergarten. Students enjoy a safe and nurturing environment and personalized attention from state-licensed teachers and highly trained educational assistants. Developmentally appropriate activities including art, motor skills, and language development, are provided within a structured learning environment where children have the opportunity to build self-esteem and positive social experiences. Learn more at https://www.maranausd.org/PAL #maranaschools

post_text: Play and Learn (PAL) is an integrated inclusive licensed preschool program providing the highest quality education to children with identified learning challenges and their Peer Model non-disabled peers, three years of age until eligible for Kindergarten. Students enjoy a safe and nurturing environment and personalized attention from state-licensed teachers and highly trained educational assistants. Developmentally appropriate activities including art, motor skills, and language development, are provided within a structured learning environment where children have the opportunity to build self-esteem and positive social experiences. Learn more at https://www.maranausd.org/PAL #maranaschools

post_text: Play and Learn (PAL) is an integrated inclusive licensed preschool program providing the highest quality education to children with identified learning challenges and their Peer Model non-disabled peers, three years of age until eligible for Kindergarten. Students enjoy a safe and nurturing environment and personalized attention from state-licensed teachers and highly trained educational assistants. Developmentally appropriate activities including art, motor skills, and language development, are provided within a structured learning environment where children have the opportunity to build self-esteem and positive social experiences. Learn more at https://www.maranausd.org/PAL #maranaschools

post_text: Allocate Your Public School Tax Credit To Marana Unified School District. Donate in person or securely and conveniently online. As an Arizona tax payer, you can allocate your public school tax credit by making a donation of up to $200 / individual and $400 / married couple. This will result in a dollar-for-dollar tax credit when you file your state return. What better way to ensure Arizona's future than by investing in our young leaders? MUSD will use your donation to fund after-school tutoring, student athletics, field trips and other areas of greatest need. Learn more: http://www.maranausd.org/taxcredit ‪#‎maranaschools‬ ‪#‎aztaxcredit‬

post_text: Welcome to #maranaschools Ashley Proctor!
shared_text:
Quail Run Elementary School
August 6 at 7:49 AM ·

Hi! I'm Ashley Proctor and I am teaching 2nd Grade.

While I may be new to the teaching team, I am not new to Quail Run. My oldest just promoted out of 6th grade this past spring! Coming back to teach just feels like home and I couldn't be more proud to be a Quasar.

Even though our year is beginning virtually, I look forward to making meaningful connections with all of my students and creating memories I'm sure none of us will forget!

post_text: Welcome to #maranaschools Ms. Jefferson!
shared_text:
Dove Mountain CSTEM K-8 School
July 30 at 4:00 PM ·

Introducing a new face to our 6th grade team! Meet Ms. Jefferson!

Hello Dove Mountain Families! I am Kari Jefferson and I am new this year to Dove Mountain. I am excited to be teaching 6th grade and I look forward to getting to know you! I come to you from Carthage, Illinois where I was a 7/8th grade math teacher for six years and a first grade teacher for one year. I decided to move to Marana this summer so my daughter and I could be closer to my brother's family. My daughter will be a fourth grader at Dove Mountain. I attended Monmouth College in Illinois and graduated with a degree in Elementary Education with an endorsement in middle school mathematics. I was also a four year varsity volleyball player for my college. I love being outdoors and staying active and am looking forward to the warmer weather. I am so happy to become a Jaguar!

post_text: Welcome to #maranaschools Mrs. Marshall!
shared_text:
Dove Mountain CSTEM K-8 School
July 29 at 10:00 AM ·

We are excited to welcome Mrs. Marshall to the Dove Mountain team!

Hi from Meaghan Marshall, the new part-time special education teacher. Hailing from western NY, but a happy desert dweller since 2006, I am thrilled to join the staff at Dove Mountain this year. In my 13 years as an educator I have worked in public and private schools and with students from grade K-12. I love teaching, reading, travelling, adventuring, hiking, organizing, and my family (p.s. Go Red Sox!). My husband and I have 2 wonderful children at Dove Mountain and the incredible experience they had last year impressed me, playing a big part in my desire to be part of the Jaguar Team.

I believe that if you feel a balance of excitement and nerves about a new endeavor you’re in the right place and space. Education is not currently what anyone has experienced before and I am feeling the energy and the butterflies, so I know I’m in a good place!

post_text: Welcome to #maranaschools Jordan Kaminsky!
shared_text:
Roadrunner Elementary School
July 22 at 5:00 PM ·

Roadrunner spotlight!

Join us in welcoming Jordan Kaminsky to our Roadrunner family. Mr. Kaminsky will be joining our team as the new librarian and comes to us with many years of experience working in libraries and classrooms both here and abroad.

I began my education career as a classroom teacher in my home town of Lincoln Nebraska. I was an elementary librarian in Lincoln as well as in Phoenix and Mesa.

Working for Chandler Public Library I was a librarian in the Basha branch library. This past year I taught 4th grade in the Tucson School District. I'm looking forward to sharing great books with my new Roadrunner friends.

#maranaschools

post_text: #maranaschools encourages all parents/guardians to pick up a district-owned Chromebook for each enrolled student. If your student still has the one loaned in March, great...those are the same computers students will use beginning August 5 when the school year begins. Check with your student’s school for Chromebook distribution dates/times. Not only will it be beneficial for every student to have their own device rather than sharing with family members, but we have also found that many of the District’s specific learning applications and security features only work on Chrome. #MUSDChoice #MUSDSafeReturn #MUSDStaysConnected

post_text: Play and Learn (PAL) is an integrated inclusive licensed preschool program providing the highest quality education to children with identified learning challenges and their Peer Model non-disabled peers, three years of age until eligible for Kindergarten. Students enjoy a safe and nurturing environment and personalized attention from state-licensed teachers and highly trained educational assistants. Developmentally appropriate activities including art, motor skills, and language development, are provided within a structured learning environment where children have the opportunity to build self-esteem and positive social experiences. Learn more at https://www.maranausd.org/PAL #maranaschools

post_text: Allocate Your Public School Tax Credit To Marana Unified School District. Donate in person or securely and conveniently online. As an Arizona tax payer, you can allocate your public school tax credit by making a donation of up to $200 / individual and $400 / married couple. This will result in a dollar-for-dollar tax credit when you file your state return. What better way to ensure Arizona's future than by investing in our young leaders? MUSD will use your donation to fund after-school tutoring, student athletics, field trips and other areas of greatest need. Learn more: http://www.maranausd.org/taxcredit ‪#‎maranaschools‬ ‪#‎aztaxcredit‬

post_text: The McKinney-Vento Homeless Assistance Act is a federal law that provides support and resources for students whose families are experiencing homelessness to help ensure that they have an equal opportunity for success in school. Any child who lacks "a fixed, regular and adequate nighttime residence" may qualify for services, including those sharing the housing of others, living in transitional shelters, and more. Learn specifics on who qualifies and a child's guaranteed rights at https://www.maranausd.org/homeless. #maranaschools
